                     1 copy of Rudimenta linguae persicae by Javier, Jerónimo, 1549-1617
                  </summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_12198-item1">
                     <author key="person_51096485" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/51096485" role="aut" change="#role-assignment">
                        <persName type="standard">Javier, Jerónimo, 1549-1617</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="la" key="work_10057">Rudimenta linguae persicae</title>
                     <note>A Persian grammar in Latin. Followed on ff.16-109 by a Latin-Portuguese-Persian vocabulary, arranged in order of Latin words. The Persian words are in both Persian and Roman scripts. Ff.110-121 contain a number of similar vocabularies on special subjects, beginning "Nomina Theologica necessaria ad explicationem Misteriorum SSmae Trinitatis..." The name of the author has apparently been cut out of f.14. Ascription to Jerónimo Javier is suppositious</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="la">Latin, Portuguese and Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
